        <div>
          <h2 class="fw-light">
            <br />
            Why more number of road accidents happening in India?
            </h1>
            <br />
            <p>
              According to the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways, in 2020, India witnessed a considerable number of road accidents, injuries, and fatalities. In 2020, a total of 4,39,768 road accidents were reported, resulting in 1,54,732 deaths and 4,51,361 injuries. These figures indicate the magnitude of the road safety challenge in the country.

              It's important to note that the Indian government has been taking steps to address road safety issues and reduce the number of accidents. These initiatives include awareness campaigns, stricter enforcement of traffic laws, improvement of road infrastructure, and promotion of safer driving practices.
            </p>

            <p>
              Several factors contribute to the high number of road accidents in India. Some of the key reasons are:

              <p><b>->Poor infrastructure</b>: Many roads in India lack proper maintenance, signage, lighting, and safety measures, which can increase the risk of accidents.</p>

              <p><b>->Rapid urbanization</b>: India is experiencing rapid urbanization, leading to an increase in the number of vehicles on the roads. The existing infrastructure struggles to cope with the growing volume of traffic, resulting in congestion and accidents.</p>

              <p><b>->Non-adherence to traffic rules</b>: Violation of traffic rules is a significant factor contributing to road accidents in India. Common violations include overspeeding, drunk driving, reckless driving, not wearing seat belts or helmets, jumping red lights, and overtaking in a dangerous manner.</p>

              <p><b>->Lack of road safety awareness</b>: There is a need for more extensive road safety education and awareness campaigns targeting all road users, including drivers, pedestrians, and cyclists. Many people in India have limited knowledge of traffic rules and safe driving practices.</p>

              <p><b>->Inadequate law enforcement</b>: While there are traffic laws and regulations in place, the enforcement of these laws can be inconsistent. Strengthening law enforcement efforts, including stricter penalties for traffic violations, can act as a deterrent.</p>

              <p><b>->Poor vehicle maintenance</b>: Many vehicles on Indian roads are poorly maintained, leading to mechanical failures that can cause accidents.</p>

              <p><b>->Diverse road users</b>: India has a diverse mix of road users, including pedestrians, cyclists, two-wheelers, three-wheelers, cars, trucks, and buses. The interaction between these different types of vehicles and the varying behavior of road users can contribute to accidents.</p>
              
            </p>

            <h3>An Overview of the Total Accidents in India in the year 2020</h3>
            <p>
              Representing four types of accidents state wise over the country in the year 2020.
            </p>
